  "body": "# Feature Issue\n\n[Figma Design](https://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=15331-288514&mode=design&t=mGXKgDSgRz01Czk4-0)\n\n### User Story\n\n- As a user\n- I want to be able to selectively share my account addresses\n- So that I can keep some of them private\n\n\n\n![Image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/5999878/dacc8490-ec92-444a-bb70-2eb92d93a17f)\n\n\n\n### Description\n\nThis feature enables users to selectively share their account addresses within the application, enhancing user privacy and control. Users with multiple addresses can choose which ones are visible to others, aligning with various privacy needs and preferences.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Follow Figma\n- Users should be able to selectively share individual account addresses, with clear controls for setting each address as public or private.\n\n\n",
